text:
The Tinder line this man used that's left thousands of women wanting to date him "I call myself Jared..." Get daily updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
A man called Jared is throwing darts and breaking hearts. Because he can. And people love it. 
Jared's profile states that he's a 19-year-old student at the University of Florida . 
Like millions of others, the teenager uses Tinder . His bio reads: "I call myself Jared, but you can call me tonight". Hi Jared (Photo: @rllynatalia/Twitter) 
You can't, actually, because you don't have his number. But a girl called Natalia might. She stumbled upon Jared on Monday, and shared his profile with the world. 
Natalia tweeted Jared's profile, along with the collection of photos he's posted. Read More Woman uses heartbreaking opening line on all her Tinder matches - gets a variety of responses 
Accompanying his strapline, Jared is pictured throwing a dart onto a postcard on a dartboard. The postcard reads: "Your heart". Classic. 
You might think Jared a little cheesy. Arrogant, even. His smile in his fourth profile photo is definitely not for everyone. But most people are enjoying his confidence. And his apparent ability to throw an arrow straight and true. Girls want Jared. Guys want to be Jared. There's now a Spanish Jared. 
But...where is Jared? Oh. Here he is . According to his Twitter profile, he's now graduated, is a billionaire, and he lives in Tampa, Florida. His DMs are open. Feel free to slide in. poll loading Would you swipe right on Jared? 0+ VOTES SO FAR
